  "text": "Observe that φ n,2 = φ n − ,2 · t a , and consider the map G : HF (−M n,2 ) → HF (−M n − ,2 ) induced by the corresponding Stein 2-handle cobordism (or, equivalently, by −1-surgery on a copy of the curve a in the open book for M n − ,2 ). To understand G, it helps to think of M n,d and M n − ,d as the branched double covers Σ(B n,d ) and Σ(B n − ,d ). Note that B n,d is obtained from B n − ,d by taking the oriented resolution of B n − ,d at a negative crossing. Let us denote the unoriented resolution at this crossing by B u n − ,d . It is not hard to see that B u n − ,d is an alternating link and does not depend on d. Moreover, the double covers of S 3 branched along these braids fit into the surgery exact triangle below (for d = 2) [CITATION_1] . ",
